            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "# Status\n\n- ✅ \"Command-line arguments to attach to a running nvim instance and start the text UI.\" `:help --remote-ui`.\n- ✅ `:detach` command. #32385\n    - Works with all UIs (TUI/GUI).\n    - The builtin `nvim` TUI spawns the `nvim --embed` child (server) with \"detach\". So `:detach` can close the channel and leave the server running.\n\n# Todo\n\n- Detach via `[count]<c-z>`: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/30319\n- \"A command-line argument to list running nvim instances.\"\n- sort by most-recent, so it's easy to reattach after detach.\n- \"hot swap\": `:connect [address]` (or `:attach`?) detaches the current UI and attaches to `[address]`. If `[address]` is not given, present a menu of known servers.\n    - To support \"hot swap\" I assume/hope that we can simply update `ui_client_attach` to accept an arbitrary channel: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/a30afeeb85176b83f3f540851218165e5d9c4c47/src/nvim/ui_client.c#L83\n\n# Implementation\n\nHere's a sketch of how `:connect` could be implemented, based on the implementation of `:restart`:\n\n1. implement `:connect` as a new `ex_connect` function. \n    - It can call out to Lua to do most of the logic.\n    - When the user selects a server from the list (or by passing an arg `:connect <address>`), the logic emits a `connect` UI-event which contains the address. See [remote_ui_restart](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/cd06e0c9d6bea2d91b553c2552e4654d2040480b/src/nvim/api/ui.c#L268) for a starting point.\n2. the ui-client handles the `connect` UI event, similar to it [handles the `restart` UI event](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/cd06e0c9d6bea2d91b553c2552e4654d2040480b/src/nvim/ui_client.c#L291).\n3. the ui-client attaches to the server address (for a starting point, see [how it attaches after a \"restart\" UI event](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/cd06e0c9d6bea2d91b553c2552e4654d2040480b/src/nvim/ui_client.c#L340-L342)) ",
